Documentation.Data: Name of your data space. It can be e.g. name of your team, company or a project, depending on what information you will store there. You can see it in the top-left corner of the screen.

SchemaItem.Name: 00010_Database_Entity_OrigamDataSpace
SchemaItem.M01: IF NOT EXISTS (SELECT * FROM INFORMATION_SCHEMA.TABLES WHERE TABLE_NAME = N'OrigamDataSpace') CREATE TABLE [OrigamDataSpace] ( [Logo] IMAGE NULL, [Name] NVARCHAR(50) NOT NULL, [RecordCreatedBy] UNIQUEIDENTIFIER NULL, [RecordUpdatedBy] UNIQUEIDENTIFIER NULL, [Id] UNIQUEIDENTIFIER NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY NONCLUSTERED, [RecordCreated] DATETIME NULL, [RecordUpdated] DATETIME NULL)

SchemaItem.Name: 00020_DefaultSpace
SchemaItem.M01: IF (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM OrigamDataSpace) = 0 INSERT INTO OrigamDataSpace (Id, Name) VALUES ('00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000', 'No Space')
